  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">There is a refugee crisis at Europe&apos;s door. The reason we talk about a &quot;crisis&quot; is not because of the number of refugees but because of the incapacity of Europe to deal with the problem in an organized and predictable way. There is a need for all European countries to cooperate with solidarity in order to confront this problem with cooperation and goodwill. The Greek islands receive 2.500 refugees every day. Source:  The Greek Police Site and the UNHCR</narrative>
  </description>
